cs.MS, cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is a likely category as the paper presents an analytic framework for formulating the statistical distribution of the nearest neighbour distance in hard-core point processes. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category as the paper deals with deriving the cumulative distribution function of the contact distance in three cases, which involves information theory concepts. 
- cs.DM (Data Mining) is a possible category as the paper deals with statistical distribution of nearest neighbour distance, which is a common problem in data mining. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper tests the analytic results against Monte-Carlo simulations, which involves numerical analysis. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper deals with point processes, which are commonly used in modeling social and information networks.
